body:
I managed to find where the issue is originated. I'm trying to return the internal Stack Trace of my custom exception via Metadata.

I implemented the Greeter Example using Grpc.Core, and modified the `SayHello` method

```csharp
public override Task<HelloReply> SayHello(HelloRequest request, ServerCallContext context)
{
    try
    {
        RecursiveMethod(4);
    }
    catch(Exception)
    {
        var metadata = new Metadata();
        metadata.Add("stack_trace", exc.StackTrace);
        throw new RpcException(
            status: new Status(StatusCode.InvalidArgument, "Custom details"),
            trailers: metadata,
            message: "Custom Message"
        );
    }
}
private void RecursiveMethod(int iteration)
{
    if(iteration < 1)
    {
        throw new Exception("Custom Exception!");
    }
    RecursiveMethod(iteration -1);
}
```
This exception generate the following stack trace (722 chars length):

```
at Greeter.Service.GreeterImpl.RecursiveMethod(Int32 iteration) in ~/Desktop/app/Services/GreeterImpl.cs:line 45
   at Greeter.Service.GreeterImpl.RecursiveMethod(Int32 iteration) in ~/Desktop/app/Services/GreeterImpl.cs:line 45
   at Greeter.Service.GreeterImpl.RecursiveMethod(Int32 iteration) in ~/Desktop/app/Services/GreeterImpl.cs:line 45
   at Greeter.Service.GreeterImpl.RecursiveMethod(Int32 iteration) in ~/Desktop/app/Services/GreeterImpl.cs:line 45
   at Greeter.Service.GreeterImpl.RecursiveMethod(Int32 iteration) in ~/Desktop/app/Services/GreeterImpl.cs:line 45
   at Greeter.Service.GreeterImpl.SayHello(HelloRequest request, ServerCallContext context) in ~/Desktop/app/Services/GreeterImpl.cs:line 51
```

And receive a `Cancelled` status on the client side. If I set to 0 the parameter passed to `RecursiveMethod` (reducing the length of the stack trace), o remove the metadata from the generated `RpcEception`, the client receives the custom RpcException.

Is there any limitation on the metadata?
